item.title: Toyota increases share in US auto market (Manila Bulletin)
item.description: DETROIT (AP) â€” With a model lineup that consumers love, Toyota Motor Corp. continued to take market share from other automakers last month, posting an industry-best 17 percent increase in sales.

item.title: ANALYSIS - North Korea finds market for missiles shrinking (Reuters via Yahoo! Asia News)
item.description: SEOUL (Reuters) - The missile market is not what it used to be for North Korea, with fewer buyers for a key export product and a loss in prestige when its top-end rocket fizzled after a short test flight, U.S. officials and experts said.

item.title: Broward labor market's a solid performer (Miami Herald)
item.description: In looking at South Florida's labor market, it's a tale of two cities, with Fort Lauderdale coming out on top, by far, according to an annual Labor Day report by Florida International University's Bruce Nissen.

item.title: NID to help Jharkhand e-market crafts (Yahoo! India News)
item.description: Ranchi, Sep 3 (IANS) Jharkhand will e-market its indigenous products with the help of National Institute of Design (NID), Ahmedabad.

item.title: Reinsurance market goes high-tech to predict disasters (The Herald-Tribune)
item.description: Hurricane outlooks are closely watched at such places as the Lloyd's of London insurance market building.

item.title: Government warned against going into property market (Sunday Business Post)
item.description: A new report is expected to warn the Government not to intervene in the property market. The report by IIB Bank, which is due to be published tomorrow, will argue that it doesn't make sense for the Government to try and stop speculators buying new homes for profit.

item.title: Farmers Market gets shoulder-to-shoulder crowds on Saturdays (Great Falls Tribune)
item.description: The produce is bountiful at the Great Falls Farmers Market and so are the customers, vendors say. "Business is booming," said Heather Sands of Little Creek Nursery in Fort Shaw.

item.title: City Hall takes Plan B for SF market rehab (Sun Star)
item.description: CITY OF SAN FERNANDO -- The City Government here shelved an earlier proposal of constructing the old public market through a bond flotation scheme and instead took Plan B, which is the rehabilitation of the market's wet section.

item.title: Market watch (AG Weekly)
item.description: The Market Sentiment Index can be an invaluable tool in forecasting important price tops and bottoms in the market. The index was developed by Market Vane, a California-based research company, in the 1960s and is still published by a variety of reliable sources.

item.title: Catholic War Vets Ladies Club sets flea market (Times Leader)
item.description: Catholic War Veterans, Post 274, Ashley, Ladies Club will hold a flea market from 7 a.m. until 2 p.m. Sept. 10, Sept. 24 and Oct. 1 on the grounds of the Catholic War Veterans. The event will take place rain or shine. For more information, vendor information or to reserve a table, call Marsha Panetta at 823-6232 or Dorothy Liberaski at 474-9969.
